data.title: Minneapolis StarTribune
data.meta_description: Minneapolis StarTribune - a place for remembering loved ones; a space for sharing memories, life stories, milestones, to express condolences, and celebrate life of your loved ones
data.text:
Bart Duffy

Bart Joseph Duffy, age 62, of Fridley, passed away on August 7, 2024, surrounded by family and loved ones.

H. Lorraine Olson

Olson, H. Lorraine passed away on 8/10/2024. Preceded in death by husband of 56 years, Rueben; parents; 4 brothers; and son-in-law. Survived by daughters, Nancy Heer and Joan (Vernon) DeBlieck; four grandchildren; and seven great-grandchildren. Interment Ft. Snelling National Cemetery. Funeral service...

Patricia Schwartz

Schwartz, Patricia Ann (Broderson) 85, Edina, passed away on August 2, 2024, in Marathon, FL. She was preceded in death by her husband, Sheldon and parents, Earl and Lenore and sister, Eleane Story. She was born on October 9, 1938, in Yankton, SD. After graduation she went to work for Capital Airlines in...

Teresa Smith

Teresa passed away on August 2, 2024 at the age of 94. Teresa was born to James D.F. and Teresa Smith in Cherokee, Iowa on April, 28, 1930, 94 years ago. In 1945, after WWII, Teresa's parents moved the family from Cherokee to St. Paul. Teresa graduated from St. Paul Central High School in 1948. She played basketball...

Jolene Taylor

With heavy hearts we announce the passing of Jolene Taylor, who left this world on Aug. 4, 2024, in Columbia Heights, MN. Jolene was born on Feb. 7, 1947, in Minneapolis, MN. She was a beloved wife to Warren Taylor. A funeral service will be held from 10:00 AM to 12:00 PM on 2024-08-13 at Miller Funeral Home &...

William Ulrich

William Arthur Ulrich passed away on July 16, 2024, due to complications from a broken neck in Tucson, AZ. He is survived by his wife of 54 years, Carol Ulrich; his sister, Sandy; three brothers-in-law; and eight nieces and nephews. He will be greatly missed by all at Ulrich Motors in Minneapolis.

Wayne Allen

Allen, Wayne C. age 90, of Howard Lake passed away on 7/28/24. He served in the US Navy from 1953- 1956. He worked at Honeywell Aerospace in Mpls, and retired from FMC/BAE in 1992. Wayne was active in BSA Troop 206 and Trinity Lutheran Church, Long Lake. He enjoyed time with family, camping, hunting and...

Ingrid Erica White

Ingrid Erica White June 17, 1977 to August 12, 2014 Though you are no longer with us, you will never be forgotten.

Jan Boylan

Four years and still deeply missed "so much bad." Until we meet again mama, may you sing with the angels and continue to feel our love

Jill & Kelly

ELEANOR I. WALIOR

ELEANOR I. WALIOR Dec. 29, 1938 - Aug. 8, 2011 Forever in our hearts; your memories are treasured every day. Your husband, children, grandchildren, family and friends miss you

KEN "KENNY" CZUPTA

KEN "KENNY" CZUPTA Aug. 5, 1968 Aug. 20, 2006 Hi Ken, Tomorrow would be your 56th Birthday, August 5, 1968. You were actually born on a Monday. Wishing you a very Happy Birthday. Love, Love, Love You! Mom, David, Cindy, Family & Friends

Adam Engman-Delforge

Adam Engman-Delforge 8/4/80 - 3/28/03 "If I could turn back time, If I could find a way, If I could reach the stars, I'd give 'em all to you." I remember you every day, but especially on your birthday. Love you forever, Your Mother

Brian Toivonen

Brian Toivonen Happy Birthday! Love Always, Mom XOXO "May you see the reflection of your life's kindness and beauty in all the tears that fall for you." Send a kid skiing - http://Give.RidingOnInsulin.org/brian

Joy Whipps

In Memory of Joy Whipps 10/7/46 - 7/31/04 It's been 20 years since you left us. Time has gone so fast but our love has not. We will always love you. Love, Bob and best friend Patricia.

Raymond B. Anthony

Raymond B. Anthony March 11, 1952 - July 29, 2022 My little brother and best friend. I miss our weekly phone calls when we discussed every topic under the sun. I miss your willingness to always help others and how you always looked out for me. You will always be in our hearts.
